shared_text:
Seton Education Partners
April 1 at 4:37 PM ·

What does #LivingHope look like? It looks like Reyes Claudio, mother of 4 and senior director of operations for Brilla Public Charter Schools working til 9 p.m. on a Friday Night equipping more than 650 families in the South Bronx with computers, books, internet and essential supplies amidst the closing of schools this month...and then staying up to feed her 4-week-old baby throughout the night.

Living Hope is Reyes, along with her school-based operations team, serving with a deep sense of JOY. She was where she was meant to be, where she was needed—comforting others during a time of great fear.

Learn more about Reyes’ story of #LivingHope here: https://www.setonpartners.org/news/living-hope/mott-haven/

Attention families, due to COVID-19, the NYC Dept. of Education has announced that schools will be closed until at least April 20th. In line with our policy of following DOE closures, all Brilla Schools will also remain closed until April 20th. We understand the extreme impact this has on our scholars and families, and we will support you all in this unprecedented and challenging time.

Atención familias, debido a COVID-19, el Departamento de Educación de Nueva York ha anunciado que las escuelas estarán cerradas hasta al menos el 20 de abril. De acuerdo con nuestra póliza de seguir los cierres del DOE, todas las Escuelas Brilla también permanecerán cerradas hasta el 20 de abril. Entendemos el impacto extremo que esto tiene en nuestros estudiantes y familias, y los apoyaremos a todos en este momento sin precedentes y desafiante.
